    <item>
      <title>Xterm like Control-L in Eshell</title>
      <link>https://blog.chmouel.com/2006/12/27/xterm-like-control-l-in-eshell/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 28 Dec 2006 00:00:15 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://blog.chmouel.com/2006/12/27/xterm-like-control-l-in-eshell/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;If you want to emulate Control-L in Eshell (the Emacs Shell) like in Xterm, you can use this :&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-lisp&#34; data-lang=&#34;lisp&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;defun&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;eshell-show-minimum-output&lt;/span&gt; ()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;interactive&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;goto-char&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;eshell-beginning-of-output&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;set-window-start&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;selected-window&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;		    (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;save-excursion&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;		      (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;goto-char&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;point-max&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;		      (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;line-beginning-position&lt;/span&gt;)))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;eshell-end-of-output&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;And add a key bind to it in your custom hook :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-lisp&#34; data-lang=&#34;lisp&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;local-set-key&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;\C-l&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;eshell-show-minimum-output&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Cheetah Mode for Emacs</title>
      <link>https://blog.chmouel.com/2006/07/31/cheetah-mode-for-emacs/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 31 Jul 2006 23:35:09 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://blog.chmouel.com/2006/07/31/cheetah-mode-for-emacs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Here is a simple html derived mode for &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.cheetahtemplate.org/&#34;&gt;Cheetah&lt;/a&gt; templates files. The font-locking regexp can be improved thought but thatâ€™s a start.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-lisp&#34; data-lang=&#34;lisp&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;define-derived-mode&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;cheetah-mode&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#8be9fd;font-style:italic&#34;&gt;html-mode&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f1fa8c&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;Cheetah&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
